2nd row<p>Ichigo is kicked out of the Royal Palace after failing his test and finds himself in the Human World. There he is visited by his father, who tells him the story of Ichigo's mother, Masaki Kurosaki.</p>
3rd row<p>Challis Court seems to be a tight-knit community for retired police officers, but hierarchies from the force have remained--and resentments. When a new arrival is found dead, the other residents regard a murder on their doorstep as an affront and a challenge. Since Challis is a gated estate, Barnaby realizes that the killer is likely a resident… and therefore an ex-police officer.</p>
4th row<p>Trad Ar Fad embarks on a journey to one of the most exciting folk festivals, the Festival Interceltique de Lorient. Throughout ten days in early August, the festival showcases Celtic music and culture from a range of countries. It has been described as a melting pot like no other, and through the lens of Trad Ar Fad, we capture the atmosphere around the venues and other locations with Caoimhe Ní Chathail as our guide. This episode includes performances from Rura, The Bonny Men, Ross Ainslie and more.</p>
5th row<p>Caoimhe Ní Chathail introduces performances from the Festival Interceltique de Lorient, and we get a sense of the festival atmosphere as we stroll around the venues and locations. Featuring music from Ímar, The Karan Casey Band, Ards Comhaltas Branch, Dónal O'Connor and more.</p>
